"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/513044","Home Office","false","2016-04-19","<p>There is regular dialogue with the UNHCR on a range of migration issues.</p><p>Discussions have included Calais and the Dublin Regulation. Processing of these cases, however, remain the responsibility of the French and UK Governments.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2016-04-19T17:10:35.6Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/513044/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/513044/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/513044/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/513044/answer/previousversion/56020","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/513044/answer/previousversion/56020",,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-04-14","Asylum: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what offers of support the Government has received from the United Nations High Commission for Refugees for the processing of take charge requests under the Dublin regulations for people resident in the camp at Calais; and what response the Government has given to each such offer.","false","Biography information for Stuart C. McDonald","Cumbernauld, Kilsyth and Kirkintilloch East","Stuart C. McDonald","34081"
