"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512402","Attorney General","false","2016-04-19","<p>The Serious Fraud Office (SFO) is an intelligence led agency and follows the National Intelligence Model (NIM) when sharing information with law enforcement partners.</p><p>Every report made to the SFO is assessed by a member of its Intelligence Unit in conjunction with other information available. The SFO passes information on to others when it has appropriate intelligence to share. This could be information from a single report, or a collated intelligence package.</p><p>The vast majority of reports made to the SFO are not matters which it can investigate, and are more appropriate for the police or other agencies. Action Fraud is the UK's national fraud reporting centre. Individuals are asked to report matters directly to them so that Action Fraud can make best use of their information. They will also be given a crime report number for future reference.</p><p>The table below shows the minimum number of intelligence referrals made by the SFO to other agencies which are directly referable to reports made through the dedicated reporting channel(1) since these statistics have been recorded. It also shows the number of SFO investigations opened since 2012 where the initial report to the SFO came through its online reporting system.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Number of referrals</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>SFO investigations that originated through online reporting system</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>Not recorded</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>Not recorded</p></td><td><p>2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>144</p></td><td><p>3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>154</p></td><td><p>3</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>1. The SFO does not record statistical information about all types of referrals that it makes to other agencies that are directly referable to reports made through the dedicated reporting channel, so the total number may be higher.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright","33834 ; 33835","2016-04-19T17:02:50.54Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512402/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512402/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512402/answer",,,,,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2016-04-13","Fraud","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, pursuant to the Answer of 11 April 2016 to Question 32551, how many reports from the dedicated reporting channel were deemed to have enough information to warrant opening an investigation in each year since 2012.","false","Biography information for Karl Turner","Kingston upon Hull East","Karl Turner","33836"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512403","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-19","<p>The number of civil servants employed by each agency of the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills is shown in the attached table and represents the position as at 31 December 2015. The Department does not hold centrally any location data for its agencies prior to this date.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-04-19T14:54:41.633Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512403/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512403/answer","Attachment to 33805.xlsx","Attachment to 33805","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512403/answer","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512403/answer/previousversion/55902","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512403/answer/previousversion/55902",,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-04-13","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many civil servants were employed by each agency of his Department in each location in the last year for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","33805"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512405","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-18","<p>The Department of Business, Innovation and Skills launched a public consultation - <em>Moving Land Registry operations into the private sector</em>, on 24 March 2016. This public consultation will remain open for nine weeks until 26 May to allow public and stakeholders to respond to it.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-04-18T14:48:48.613Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512405/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512405/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512405/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-04-13","Land Registry: Privatisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, with reference to paragraph 1.302 of the Spending Review and Autumn Statement 2015, what progress his Department has made on consulting on options to move operations of the Land Registry to the private sector from 2017.","false","Biography information for Michelle Donelan","Chippenham","Michelle Donelan","33822"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512406","Department for Transport","false","2016-04-18","<p>There are no plans to legislate for car manufacturers to incorporate waste bins in the design of their cars. Most cars already have a variety of suitable storage facilities for drivers and passengers to store waste items.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-04-18T15:11:13.08Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512406/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512406/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512406/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-04-13","Cars: Waste Disposal","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will bring forward legislative proposals to ensure car manufacturers incorporate waste bins in the design of their cars.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","33830"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512407","HM Treasury","false","2016-04-22","<p>The time taken to resolve an appeal can be affected by a number of factors, such as the complexity of the case or whether the case proceeds to be listed for hearing by the independent Valuation Tribunal. Some cases can be held up in litigation or placed on hold at the ratepayer's request. The average (median) time taken to resolve challenges for non-domestic properties in each of the last five years is shown in the attached table. This table covers the 2010 Local Rating Lists.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Median (days)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010-11</p></td><td><p>135<sup>*</sup></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>335</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>413</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>390</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>395</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p>*The 2010 list began on 1 April 2010 so only those challenges received in 2010-11 were resolved in 2010-11. In subsequent years, however, challenges received in previous years can also be resolved so the median clearance time may include more complex challenges which took longer to resolve.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-04-22T10:13:50.003Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512407/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512407/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512407/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-13","Non-domestic Rates: Appeals","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the average length of a non domestic rates appeal was in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","33839"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512408","HM Treasury","false","2016-04-22","<p>HM Treasury does not hold information on the number or profile of over-indebted consumers, nor is there any universally agreed definition of what constitutes an over-indebted consumer.</p><p> </p><p>The Money Advice Service (MAS) has statutory responsibility to assist members of the public with the management of debt, and within this remit MAS publishes data on the levels of over-indebtedness in the UK. Their most recent report, A Picture of Over-Indebtedness, estimates the statistical likelihood of individuals being over indebted based on a number of characteristics and is available online:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.moneyadviceservice.org.uk/en/corporate/a-picture-of-over-indebtedness" target="_blank">https://www.moneyadviceservice.org.uk/en/corporate/a-picture-of-over-indebtedness</a></p><p> </p><p>The technical report includes detailed data and a description of the methodology, and is also available online:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://masassets.blob.core.windows.net/cms/files/000/000/336/original/MAS_PictureOverindebtedness_TechnicalReport_March2016.pdf" target="_blank">https://masassets.blob.core.windows.net/cms/files/000/000/336/original/MAS_PictureOverindebtedness_TechnicalReport_March2016.pdf</a></p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-04-22T10:18:30.773Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512408/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512408/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512408/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-13","Debts","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many over-indebted consumers there were from each socio-economic group in the most recent period for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","33840"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512409","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-22","<p>Table 1 sets out the total funding provided to the Department’s partner organisations for each financial year since 2009-10. Funding includes grant-in-aid funding or an increased equity investment.</p><p>Table 2 sets out these partner organisations according to type and sector. <br> <br> Since 2010 the Department has significantly reduced its number of partner organisations down to 44. We committed to further reductions as part of the BIS2020 programme of departmental transformation to make the Department cheaper and simpler, and to deliver better services to users.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-04-22T12:40:07.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512409/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512409/answer","Word Version of Supporting Table for PQ (EF).doc","Partner organisation funding statistics","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512409/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-04-13","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills: Public Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how much funding his Department provided to each of its partner organisations in each year from 2010; and what the (a) type and (b) sector of those organisations is.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","33841"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512411","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-20","<p>Output per worker was approximately 2.2% higher in 2015 compared to 2008, according to the Office for National Statistics. On an output per hour basis, productivity was 1.7% higher in 2015 compared to 2008.</p><p>Increasing productivity growth remains one of the key economic challenges for this Parliament. The government’s ‘Fixing the Foundations’ productivity plan sets out the ambitious vision and pro-productivity agenda that the government is working on to meet the productivity challenge that most advanced economies face.</p><p>The productivity plan can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/fixing-the-foundations-creating-a-more-prosperous-nation" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/fixing-the-foundations-creating-a-more-prosperous-nation</a></p><p>As the plan notes, every part of government is contributing to this ambition; and the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills is working across Whitehall to ensure that the reforms set out in the plan are delivered with urgency and pace.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-04-20T15:03:03.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512411/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512411/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512411/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-04-13","Productivity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps he is taking to increase productivity to levels recorded in 2008.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","33842"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512412","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-26","<p>BIS officials have engaged with counterparts in China over the past three years to support the growing UK-China relationship and advance UK interests. During the course of those engagements they received at different times the standard hospitality associated with Government to Government exchanges. In 2010, Cabinet Office issued guidance on Civil Servant receiving gifts and hospitality, which can be found on the GOV.UK website. The guidance states that civil servants are not required to record hospitality from other civil servants in government, the Devolved Administrations, the Palace, non-departmental public bodies or overseas government.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-04-26T13:55:57.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512412/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512412/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512412/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-04-13","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills: China","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, on what occasions officials of his Department have received hospitality from the government of China in the last three years.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","33872"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512413","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-22","<p>The UK wants to see continued support for British industry as they decarbonise. In the context of a declining EU Emissions Trading System cap it is essential that free allowances should be focussed on those sectors at greatest risk of carbon leakage. Sectors at greatest risk of carbon leakage have high carbon costs and are highly exposed to international trade.</p><p>The proposed tiering scenarios set out in the UKs position paper are indicative and do not represent a confirmed UK Government position. We recognise the concerns of the cement sector and will continue to work with them to clarify data issues and consider further scenarios to those set out in the UKs proposal.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-04-22T12:42:11.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512413/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512413/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512413/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-04-13","Cement: EU Emissions Trading Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, with reference to page one of the UK/France joint non-paper on the Implementation of Tiered Free Allocation in Phase IV of the EU Emissions Trading System, what the evidential basis is for the assumption that the UK cement industry can pass on additional costs to customers of purchasing carbon dioxide allowances without risking carbon leakage.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","33897"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512414","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-29","<p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>The Permanent Secretary has recently written to the Chairs of the Public Accounts Committee and the Business, Innovation and Skills Committee. His letter contains details of the potential maximum savings from a closure of the Department’s Sheffield office at St Paul’s Place, and can be seen at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/518244/letter-martin-donnelly-sheffield-office.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/518244/letter-martin-donnelly-sheffield-office.pdf</a>.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-04-29T13:27:03.863Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512414/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512414/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512414/answer","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512414/answer/previousversion/55903","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512414/answer/previousversion/55903",,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-04-13","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills: Hotels","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what the annual cost is of hotel stays in (a) London by policy staff from his Department's office at St Paul's Place, Sheffield and (b) Sheffield by policy staff from his Department's office at 1 Victoria Street, London.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","33916"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512416","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-19","<p>The annual cost per employee at St Paul’s Place, Sheffield is £3,190 and at 1 Victoria Street, London is £9,750.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-04-19T15:07:42.503Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512416/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512416/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512416/answer","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512416/answer/previousversion/55904","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512416/answer/previousversion/55904",,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-04-13","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills: Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what the annual cost per employee is of rent, rates and maintenance for his Department's office at (a) St Paul's Place, Sheffield and (b) 1 Victoria Street, London.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","33917"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512417","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-19","<p>The information is not readily available and could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-04-19T15:09:42.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512417/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512417/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512417/answer","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512417/answer/previousversion/55905","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512417/answer/previousversion/55905",,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-04-13","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills: Travel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what the annual cost is of policy staff (a) from his Department's office at St Paul's Place, Sheffield and (b) from his Department's office at 1 Victoria Street, London travelling to Sheffield.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","33918"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512418","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-04-19","<p>My Department does not collect or publish data relating to high street vacancy rates. There are several commercial sources of shop vacancy rates data available, including the Local Data Company and Springboard, (http://info.localdatacompany.com/vacancy-rate-report-h1-2015-summary-download) who publish overall trends in the public domain.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2016-04-19T14:53:51.06Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512418/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512418/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512418/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-04-13","Empty Property: Shops","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what the high street vacancy rate was in (a) England and (b) each region of England in each of the last six years.","false","Biography information for Michael Dugher","Barnsley East","Michael Dugher","33937"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512420","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-21","<p>The Government wants young people to have the opportunity to access high quality degree level training, whether through a full-time undergraduate route or a world-class degree apprenticeship. <br> <br> Both traditional degrees and new degree apprenticeships meet the high quality criteria expected of a higher education qualification. Degree Apprenticeships are designed by groups of employers working with higher education institutions, and provide a valuable route for people to obtain a degree-level qualification alongside training for a career, with the prospect of a job from day one</p><p><br> Degree apprenticeships will feature in the new communications campaign being launched in May, promoting the benefits of apprenticeships to employers and young people.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-04-21T15:56:52.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512420/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512420/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512420/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-04-13","Apprentices: Degrees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps his Department has taken to ensure that employers accord degree apprenticeships the same esteem as traditional university degrees.","false","Biography information for David Mackintosh","Northampton South","David Mackintosh","33938"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512422","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-19","<p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>The annual cost of rent, rates and maintenance at St Paul's Place, Sheffield is £891,694 and at 1 Victoria Street, London is £21,363,694.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-04-19T15:06:05.94Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512422/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512422/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512422/answer","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512422/answer/previousversion/55906","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512422/answer/previousversion/55906",,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-04-13","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills: Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what the annual cost is of rent, rates and maintenance for his Department's office at (a) St Paul's Place, Sheffield and (b) 1 Victoria Street, London.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","33919"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512423","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-20","<p>The Government published its Impact Assessment with a full assessment of the National Living Wage policy on 7 December 2015.</p><p>300,000 workers in the South East will directly benefit from the National Living Wage by 2020. The Department for Business, Innovation and Skills has made no detailed assessment of the benefits of the National Living Wage at local authority level.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-04-20T15:01:12.333Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512423/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512423/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512423/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-04-13","Living Wage: Southampton","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what estimate he has made of how many people in Southampton will benefit from the introduction of the national living wage.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","33926"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512424","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-20","<p>It is not possible fully to disaggregate UK Trade and Investment’s budget for all its work in each overseas market. The overall budget will be made up of costs incurred in country and funds that are not market specific.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-04-20T15:02:24.763Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512424/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512424/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512424/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-04-13","UK Trade and Investment: Europe","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what UK Trade and Investment's annual budget is for work in Europe.","false","Biography information for Sir Geoffrey Clifton-Brown","The Cotswolds","Geoffrey Clifton-Brown","33929"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512428","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-18","<p>As at 31 March 2016, the numbers of civil servants employed at each Insolvency Service location were as follows:</p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Location</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Civil Servants</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Location</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Civil Servants</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Birmingham</p></td><td><p>389</p></td><td><p>Leeds</p></td><td><p>77</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Blackpool</p></td><td><p>37</p></td><td><p>Liverpool</p></td><td><p>42</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Brighton</p></td><td><p>17</p></td><td><p>London</p></td><td><p>299</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Bristol</p></td><td><p>35</p></td><td><p>Manchester</p></td><td><p>134</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Cambridge</p></td><td><p>21</p></td><td><p>Newcastle</p></td><td><p>44</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Cardiff</p></td><td><p>46</p></td><td><p>Nottingham</p></td><td><p>37</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Chatham</p></td><td><p>37</p></td><td><p>Plymouth</p></td><td><p>35</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Croydon</p></td><td><p>56</p></td><td><p>Reading</p></td><td><p>21</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Edinburgh</p></td><td><p>36</p></td><td><p>Southampton</p></td><td><p>28</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Exeter</p></td><td><p>17</p></td><td><p>Southend-on-Sea</p></td><td><p>28</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Ipswich</p></td><td><p>42</p></td><td><p><strong>Grand Total</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>1478</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>These figures do not include 15 civil servants who were on unpaid sickness absence, career break, special leave without pay or on loan to other government departments and, therefore, were not on the Insolvency Service’s payroll on 31 March 2016.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-04-18T14:23:57.853Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512428/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512428/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512428/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-04-13","Insolvency Service: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many civil servants were employed at each location of the Insolvency Service in the last year for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","33729"
