"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512431","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-18","<p>Employees of the Student Loans Company are not classed as civil servants. The table below confirms the number of Student Loans Company employees based at each of the Company’s locations at 31 March 2016.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Location</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>No. of employees (Headcount)</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Darlington</p></td><td><p>1,413</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Glasgow City Centre</p></td><td><p>1,302</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Glasgow Hillington</p></td><td><p>75</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Home based</p></td><td><p>5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Llandudno Junction</p></td><td><p>125</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total</p></td><td><p>2,920</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-04-18T15:02:17.59Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512431/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512431/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512431/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-04-13","Student Loans Company: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many civil servants were employed at each location by the Student Loans Company in the last year for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","33751"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512433","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-18","<p>The location of the Institute for Apprenticeships will be determined in due course.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-04-18T15:16:06.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512433/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512433/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512433/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-04-13","Institute for Apprenticeships","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, where he plans to locate the Institute for Apprenticeships.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","33742"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512434","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-20","<p>The plans for BIS2020 are still being developed. We do not currently have information on which posts will be at head office in 2020.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-04-20T14:57:24.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512434/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512434/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512434/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-04-13","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what proportion of (a) members of the Senior Civil Service and (b) all officials of his Department will be based at head office on conclusion of BIS2020.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","33767"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512435","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-22","<p>Departments publish details of Ministers’ and Permanent Secretaries’ meetings with external organisations, and Special Advisors’ meetings with senior media figures. BIS transparency data is published online at <a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/collections/bis-quarterly-publications-april-to-june-2012" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/collections/bis-quarterly-publications-april-to-june-2012</a> and <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/bis-special-advisers" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/bis-special-advisers</a>.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-04-22T12:39:03.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512435/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512435/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512435/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-04-13","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills: Hanover","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what meetings (a) Ministers and (b) special advisers in his Department have had with Hanover Communications International Ltd in the last year on behalf of which clients.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","33784"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512436","Cabinet Office","false","2016-04-22","<p>We publish details of gifts and hospitality received by the most senior civil servants on a quarterly basis.</p><p>The rules for civil servants, including special advisers, on the acceptance of gifts and hospitality are set out in the Civil Service Code, Civil Service Management Code and departmental staff handbooks.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","33734","2016-04-22T09:30:56.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512436/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512436/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512436/answer",,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-04-13","Civil Servants: Codes of Practice","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what his policy is on publication of the registers of gifts and hospitality for civil servants.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","33782"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512438","Cabinet Office","false","2016-04-22","<p>This information could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-04-22T09:29:34.41Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512438/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512438/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512438/answer",,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-04-13","Cabinet Office: China","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, on what occasions (a) civil servants, (b) special advisers and (c) Ministers in his Department have received hospitality from the government of China in the last five years.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","33783"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512439","Cabinet Office","false","2016-04-20","<p>There have been no meetings between Cabinet Office officials and the European Commission Directorate-General for Communication in the last 12 months.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-04-20T09:12:55.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512439/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512439/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512439/answer",,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-04-13","Communication Directorate General","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many meetings have taken place between officials of his Department and the European Commission Directorate-General for Communication in each of the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Mrs Anne Main","St Albans","Mrs Anne Main","33746"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512440","Cabinet Office","false","2016-04-18","<p>I refer my right hon. Friend the Member for Haltemprice and Howden and the hon. Member for Clacton to the answer I gave to the hon. Member for St Albans on 18 April 2016 to UIN: 32678.</p><p>The cost of the secretariat, including the Referendum Unit, will be accounted for in the Department’s annual report and accounts.</p>","Weston-super-Mare","John Penrose","33541 ; 33619 ; 33620","2016-04-18T16:57:53.427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512440/answer","Biography information for John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512440/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512440/answer",,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-04-13","Cabinet Office Referendum Unit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many civil servants from across all Government departments and at what grade have been seconded to the Cabinet Office Referendum Unit.","false","Biography information for Mr Douglas Carswell","Clacton","Mr Douglas Carswell","33727"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512441","Cabinet Office","false","2016-04-22","<p>We publish details of gifts and hospitality received by the most senior civil servants on a quarterly basis.</p><p>The rules for civil servants, including special advisers, on the acceptance of gifts and hospitality are set out in the Civil Service Code, Civil Service Management Code and departmental staff handbooks.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","33782","2016-04-22T09:30:56.083Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512441/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512441/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512441/answer",,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-04-13","Ministerial Policy Advisers: Codes of Practice","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether his Department's guidance for civil servants on acceptance of gifts or hospitality applies to special advisers.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","33734"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512444","Cabinet Office","false","2016-04-22","<p>The Government is currently considering the conclusions put forward by the NAO in its recent report on Gifts and Hospitality.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-04-22T09:31:41.587Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512444/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512444/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512444/answer",,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-04-13","Civil Servants: Codes of Practice","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what steps he has taken to implement the recommendations of the National Audit Office investigation into the acceptance of gifts and hospitality by government officials (HC 797, 2015-16).","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","33928"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512445","Cabinet Office","false","2016-04-21","<p>The JIC regularly assess the numbers involved in fighting in Syria and their loyalties. The JIC has concluded that non-extremist opposition numbers have held up despite recent pressure. Numbers in groups fighting Daesh are likely to have increased.</p>","West Dorset","Mr Oliver Letwin",,"2016-04-21T09:16:59.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512445/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Letwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512445/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512445/answer",,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-04-13","Armed Conflict: Syria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether the Joint Intelligence Committee has revised its estimate of the number of non-extremist opposition fighters in Syria since 2 December 2015.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","33817"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512446","Cabinet Office","false","2016-04-19","<p>The Successor programme is one of 188 projects reported on the Government Major Project Portfolio (GMPP) at the time of the last Major Projects Annual Report. The Infrastructure and Projects Authority undertakes a number of activities across the 188 major projects on the GMPP, including collecting quarterly programme performance data; the arrangement of independent assurance; and, providing expert advice to project and departmental leadership. These activities do not involve the assignment of individual IPA staff to work on this project specifically, but are undertaken by a number of staff working in a range of functions across the IPA.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-04-19T09:46:31.433Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512446/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512446/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512446/answer","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512446/answer/previousversion/55815","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512446/answer/previousversion/55815",,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-04-13","Trident Submarines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many members of staff of the Infrastructure and Projects Authority have been assigned to work on the Government's Successor submarine programme; and what (a) their grades, (b) their job titles and (c) the dates of their assignment to work on that programme are.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","33827"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512447","Cabinet Office","false","2016-04-19","<p>The final costs for the Independent Commission on Freedom of Information are currently being assembled and I expect to be able to publish the information shortly.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-04-19T08:52:10.74Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512447/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512447/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512447/answer","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512447/answer/previousversion/55813","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512447/answer/previousversion/55813",,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-04-13","Commission On Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what timetable he has set for publication of information on the cost to the public purse of the Independent Commission on Freedom of Information.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","33788"
