"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512450","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-04-18","The Government welcomes observers – either from within the UK or from overseas – who wish to observe our electoral process. The Electoral Commission accredits observers who may, once accredited, observe proceedings at the poll, proceedings at the issue and receipt of postal ballot papers, and proceedings at the count. It is therefore open to parliamentarians from the Parliamentary Assembly of the Council of Europe to apply for accreditation as observers.","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2016-04-18T16:42:54.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512450/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512450/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512450/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-04-13","UK Membership of EU: Referendums","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will make it the Government's policy to invite a delegation of parliamentarians from the Parliamentary Assembly of the Council of Europe as official observers of the forthcoming EU referendum.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","33908"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512451","HM Treasury","false","2016-04-18","<p>HM Revenue and Customs, HM Treasury and the Department for Education, and their Ministers, are collaborating closely on the implementation of Tax-Free Childcare and the Extended Entitlement to free childcare for 3 and 4 year olds.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2016-04-18T16:04:59.673Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512451/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512451/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512451/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-13","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what discussions he has had with the Secretary of State for Education on raising awareness of the tax-free Childcare scheme.","false","Biography information for Mr Philip Hollobone","Kettering","Mr Philip Hollobone","33936"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512452","HM Treasury","false","2016-04-18","<p>The Treasury has not made any formal assessment of the effect of immigration on GDP in the next 10 years.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-04-18T16:59:28.493Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512452/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512452/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512452/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-13","Immigration","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 23 March 2016 to Question 31494, what information his Department holds on the potential percentage change in GDP which would result from estimated levels of immigration in the next 10 years.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","33799"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512453","HM Treasury","false","2016-04-18","<p>The data can be found in the Economic and Fiscal Outlook charts and tables – March 2016, under Chapter 5, Chart 5.6: Past and projected net migration to the UK, available here: <a href="http://budgetresponsibility.org.uk/efo/economic-fiscal-outlook-march-2016/" target="_blank">http://budgetresponsibility.org.uk/efo/economic-fiscal-outlook-march-2016/</a></p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-04-18T16:59:19.01Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512453/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512453/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512453/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-13","Immigration","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate his Department has made of the level of immigration in each of the next five years to inform its economic forecasts; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","33797"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512454","HM Treasury","false","2016-04-18","<p>The Chancellor keeps all taxes under review. However, there are no plans to introduce a tax specifically on fast food containers.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-04-18T15:59:21.083Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512454/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512454/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512454/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-13","Fast Food: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will bring forward legislative proposals to introduce tax on fast food containers.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","33831"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512455","HM Treasury","false","2016-05-09","<p>HM Revenue and Customs holds data about tax repayments to business, but does not record whether repayments are linked to CJEU decisions.</p><p> </p><p>The amount repayable is often the result of decisions in both the UK courts and CJEU and it would be impossible to accurately disaggregate how much was linked to the decisions of an individual court.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-05-09T14:35:36.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512455/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512455/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512455/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-13","Business: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the value is of tax refunds to large businesses as a result of decisions from the European Court of Justice in the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","33861"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512456","Cabinet Office","false","2016-04-18","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson","33899","2016-04-18T10:07:13.08Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512456/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512456/answer","UKSA responses to 33930 33899 .pdf","UKSA Letter to Member - Net Earnings","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512456/answer",,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-04-13","Foreign Investment in UK","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the net earnings were from direct investment in UK companies in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","33930"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512457","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-04-18","Growth in the Digital Sector (measured by GVA) between 2009 and 2014 was 26.3% (in comparison to a 20% growth of the UK Economy as a whole). According to DCMS research, the digital sector accounted for 6.9% Gross Value Added in 2010, and 7.3% in 2014.<p> </p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2016-04-18T13:10:14.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512457/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512457/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512457/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-04-13","Digital Technology","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what estimate he has made of growth of the digital economy in the last five years; and what assessment he has made of its contribution to GDP.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","33915"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512458","HM Treasury","false","2016-04-18","<p>The content of the EU VAT Action Plan is a matter for the European Commission.</p><p> </p><p>European Council Conclusions welcomed “the intention of the Commission to include proposals for increased flexibility for Member States with respect to reduced rates of VAT, which would provide the option to Member States of VAT zero rating‎ for sanitary products”.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-04-18T15:56:58.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512458/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512458/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512458/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-13","Sanitary Protection: VAT","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what information his Department holds on the reasons why the EU Action Plan on VAT consultation document issued by the European Commission on 7 April 2016 omits any reference to the decision of EU Leads of Government that the UK can remove VAT from women's sanitary products; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","33907"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512459","HM Treasury","false","2016-04-18","<p>The UK is not participating in the Financial Transaction Tax (FTT) being developed by 10 EU Member States under the enhanced cooperation procedure. The tax will not therefore be implemented in the UK.</p><p> </p><p>The Chancellor has been clear throughout negotiations that the UK will not hesitate to challenge the FTT at the Court of Justice of the European Union (CJEU) if it has an extraterritorial impact on non-participating Member States.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-04-18T15:55:56.423Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512459/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512459/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512459/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-13","Taxation: EU Action","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether the UK has received a guaranteed exemption from any EU Financial Transaction Tax.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","33905"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512460","HM Treasury","false","2016-04-18","<p>The zero rate of VAT for sanitary products will take effect as soon as possible after Royal Assent.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-04-18T15:54:24.533Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512460/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512460/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512460/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-13","Sanitary Protection: VAT","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, on what date he expects the removal of VAT from women's sanitary products to take effect.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","33906"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512462","Cabinet Office","false","2016-04-18","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson","33930","2016-04-18T10:07:13.11Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512462/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512462/answer","UKSA responses to 33930 33899 .pdf","UKSA Letter to Member - Net Earnings","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512462/answer",,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-04-13","Foreign Investment in UK","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how much was received in the UK in net earnings from direct investment in companies based outside the UK in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","33899"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512463","HM Treasury","false","2016-05-12","<p>In the last six years HM Treasury argued one case on taxation as the lead Department before the European Court of Justice. The judgment went against the UK, but the protective purpose was nevertheless served.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-05-12T09:28:25.787Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512463/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512463/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512463/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-13","Taxation: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many European Court of Justice decisions on taxation his Department has (a) won and (b) lost in the last six years.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","33850"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512465","Department of Health","false","2016-04-20","<p>The Department’s National Institute for Health Research funds the Public Health Research (PHR) programme to generate evidence to inform the delivery of non-National Health Service interventions intended to improve the health of the public and reduce inequalities in health. The programme has two workstreams: commissioned and researcher-led. The PHR commissioned workstream welcomes outline proposals in response to specific research questions prioritised for their public health importance. The application for the study ‘Understanding the impact of tobacco tax increases and tobacco industry pricing on smoking behaviours and inequalities’ was received through the researcher-led workstream and therefore did not go through a tender process via the commissioned workstream. Details of the PHR application process are available on the PHR website:</p><p> </p><p>www.nets.nihr.ac.uk/programmes/phr/application-process</p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman","33867","2016-04-20T15:16:16.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512465/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512465/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512465/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-04-13","Tobacco","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what input officials of his Department had on the commissioning of the research study on tobacco taxation and tobacco industry pricing by the Department of Health to the University of Bath awarded in September 2014.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","33864"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512468","HM Treasury","false","2016-04-18","<p>The Government carefully considers all relevant legal obligations – including the Family Test – when formulating policy. This includes policies implemented via the Finance Bill or other legislation.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-04-18T15:58:12.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512468/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512468/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/512468/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-04-13","Finance (No. 2) Bill: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if his Department will apply the family test to the Finance Bill and publish the results.","false","Biography information for Mr David Burrowes","Enfield, Southgate","Mr David Burrowes","33786"
